caption: Listen...this place is sexy and the drinks are first rate. When I'm in town, I'll try to return.
This place was a great find. The host and waitress were amazing. The food was delicious and the vibe in this place is unmatched. This is, by far, one of Chicago’s best restaurants.

Basing off food and at atmosphere alone, this is a solid 4-4.5. We show up for a 7:30 resi and have to wait 15 minutes for table. Normally not a problem , but we go to bar for drink before , but they aren’t serving drinks. Whatever. While trying to order a drink, hostess gets mad at us for attempting to go to bar. Finally get seated and take off masks . That’s a big no no even though everyone else has masks off. I get Chicago people love being told what to do, but they are mask Karen’s here big time. I asked about a cocktail and got some attitude from waitress . Food was incredible . Waitress asks if we want dessert , so we place an order. 8-12 minutes later she comes back and asks if we want dessert ?? It was also my b day and I have been around enough to know you normally get some sort of dessert (especially if you ask for one ), but nothing . I would wait to go here once Chicago opens back up full time (if ever ). Food alone was great , service was nothing to write home about
Went for happy hour. Great cocktails!

You have to come here. Food is phenomenal, drinks are exciting, and the hospitality is unmatched. Kira is the Queen, she will exponentially increase the value you get for visiting. One of my faves as a Chicago local.

Not what it once was.  Gilt has been one of my favorite places to eat in Chicago over the past few years. I have celebrated birthdays, anniversaries, you name it, here, and whenever somebody visiting Chicago asked me for a recommendation, this was the place that immediately sprung to mind. However, management has made some changes that hold Gilt back from being great and instead force it to settle for good.  First, Gilt got rid of their BYOB rule, where you they would take a glass of wine away from you as a "corkage fee" and give it to another table. This, in and of itself, isn't a huge deal, and I'm fine with paying for wine. However, it does take away a bit of the charm that made this place special.  Second, and more importantly, they redid the burrata dish on the menu. The old version had picked basil, a balsamic vinaigrette, and a tomato confit to pair with the salty cheese and grilled bread. The new version has scrapped everything except the cheese and bread. I cannot fathom why this decision was made, as it neuters both the look (you now stare at white cheese on a white plate) and the flavor (completely one dimensional) of the dish. There is no reasonable explanation for this decision other than cost-cutting, plain and simple, and this dish has transformed from one of my favorites in Chicago to something completely forgettable.  There are some changes to the menu that actually work. I was skeptical of the decision to move from bucatini to "fettucine" for the truffle pasta, but the wider noodles do pick up the sauce better. However, I would also suggest changing the name from Fettucine Alfredo as it is 1) inaccurate (this dish uses papardelle, not fettucine, and the truffle sauce is barely reminiscent of alfredo) and 2) simply conjures up the wrong image. Who wants to go to a fancy restaurant and order Fettucine Alfredo?  We still had an above average meal at Gilt, but I would be lying if I said this place is the same. The dark, romantic atmosphere has been replaced by a rather gauche, over the top 1920s theme that feels more like Disney than Gatsby. The service was fine, and I would like to commend Katie who was very helpful. And some of the food still is really good! But the magic isn't there anymore, and I hesitate to say I will come back. I'm not mad, Gilt Bar, I'm just disappointed.

Beautiful ambience and fun staff. Happy hour is a crazy good deal on Wednesdays with 1/2 off wine bottles. The sliders were tasty though nothing memorable. Would love to come back and try out a full dinner with cocktails sometime.

Really enjoyed our evening. All the food was delicious and the service was outstanding. Especially enjoyed the pumpkin pesto dish and the hot cookie with salty toffee ice cream. The staff really took care of us but watching them work the room, it is safe to say that all clients felt as if they were being treated special. Thank you for a great night.
Great atmosphere, appropriate prices and overall great 1920s vibe. Would recommend if you're visiting Chicago.
Can’t get ahold of them by phone. It just has a pre-recorded message of a guy from Southern England telling you to go online...

Host at the Gilt bar was unprofessional, not only she wouldn’t follow the reservation time, she would make preferences of who gets seated when. I’ve been in the place few times and after last night I won’t go again. I wouldn’t recommend it, make your self a favor and spend your hard earned money somewhere else
Good food
This place is amazing. The food and drink were great. The atmosphere awesome and the staff was very friendly! They make you feel like family.

We go to Gilt bar for every single anniversary, birthday, and everything in between.  Somehow they always seem to remember us. They always treat us so kindly and every single experience is memorable and wonderful. Every single employee at that restaurant puts 110% into their job and it is far and away my absolute favorite place to be.  The food. The cocktails. The ambience. The staff. I've never been so impressed and felt so welcomed at a place.  Seriously, every single person there is beyond lovely and I wish them nothing but the best. We will forever be return patrons and are beyond excited every time we go.  You've achieved the absolute peak of dining, and I could not be more impressed. Thank you for making our little celebrations all the more special.
They always make me and my wife feel like family - queer friendly and amazinggg food & drinks ✨
Well worth it. Staff was awesome. Food/drink were great. I'd gladly come back! And my girlfriend agrees!
Great bone marrow, the mushroom cabonara was over seasoned to me, but every other thing was okay.
Cozy place with soft light ambiance, well prepared cocktails and great food. Please try the brussels sprouts, they are delicious!

Gilt Bar has a very good happy hour. We went for cocktails and apps on an unseasonably warm Thursday night. Gilt has a wonderful outdoor area that is perfect for covid dining. Spaced out tables and great heating lamps. We had the $5 old fashioned, $5 wine, $5 sliders (burger and crab cake), and $5 pigs in blankets. The server was very nice and pleasant. Will definitely be back for dinner.
Rude, cocky staff. They act like they're working at a top-quality gourmet restaurant, which the Gilt Bar is not.

AMAZING lunch and dinner deals. Some of the best Italian food I've had since actual Italy. Get the Black + White pasta (it's in Italian but I forgot what it's called). It was soooooo amazing. Lunch special is usually $20 and comes w appetizer, entree, and dessert. Amazing service as well.
Good food. Nice place. Don't get the bone marrow
Hostess was very unprofessional and condescending. Your customers should not be referred to as "baby" repeatedly.

Absolutely amazing! The hostess at the entrance was full of life (in a non-annoying way) knew my name before I even gave it to her, she made us feel welcomed and comfortable. The waiter was great and not over baring. The cocktails awoken the tastebuds and the steak tar tare was hands down the best we've ever had! Will definitely come back and the staff definitely deserves a raise because they're on top of their game!!! Can't wait to come back!!!!
My favorite restaurant in the world
Excellent spot to spend time alone or talk business. Looking forward to going back again. The bill was fair for the quality of the food. Ambience reminds me of Colorado Springs area.

Still dreaming about this little speakeasy after having been there a year ago!! Everything about this place was classy and elegant! It was a perfect place for a real conversation with your friends or partner....so intimate, low lit, candles and wonderfully quiet! The food was ridiculous!! We had the best mussels we have ever had...so soft and the sauce..unreal! Also had the chicken...fab!  We had to go to a birthday party after this at a loud ping pong place, and this was the perfect start of the evening to fill us up and give us some time to connect.  Can not wait to go back!! Also...photo booth in the place on the way back out...always fun to make a memory in those
Can't go wrong for signature drinks and night life atmosphere.
Downstairs was really really nice. Fantastic place for drinks and dinner.

I was here alone on NYE while on business and ended up having quite a nice time.  The food was very rich but good, cocktails were good, and they had some decently price champagne.  Since this was my third dinner of the night (hey, got to have fun somehow), I was quite inebriated and full, however the other people there for NYE were doing their own thing.  Since I enjoy being alone, it was fun to be near the exciting loud vibe of other people, but on my own, and my server was happy to share some champagne with me for the countdown.  Based on the vibe of the staff and the decent food, I'd definitely recommend Gilt Bar.
Gilt Bar has somehow become underrated. A great atmosphere (try to sit downstairs if you can), great cocktails, attentive service, and consistent food.
Delicious. Great service

Great library hidden in the basement. Small plates were very filling, at the end of the course everyone was full. Service was fast and provided drinks just in time when the glass was getting empty ;-)
Best mussels around! The basement is gorg☆
The speakeasy room downstairs has a great intimate vibe, you can get lost in conversation for hours.

Gets super crowded, and I’ve only been here for drinks, but love their drink menu. There’s a whole section of different types of Manhattans, Old Fashioneds, etc..  The downstairs speakeasy, The Library, doesn’t take reservations and is first come first serve, but they have the same menu as upstairs.  Bonus points for photo booth downstairs!
Get yourself a cocktail and ask to sit in the basement for a speakeasy Chicago feel! Food, drinks and experience is top notch!
The cocktails and food are amazing! The service is great - would recommend. Perfect place for a date.

Took my best friend from California to the Library Bar while he's been in town for a few days last night, and we were both exceptionally impressed with the service, the phenomenal atmosphere, and the drinks couldn't have been better. There's no doubt that this is the best bar for classic, intimate atmosphere in Chicago, and would highly recommend it.

My wife and I spent our valentine's day out this year and opted to adventure out to this wonderful restaurant. The atmosphere was very chill, the cocktails perfectly balanced and our meals were some of the best plates we've had in the city.  The entire experience was topped off with wonderful service.  Highly recommended.

I had dinner at gilt bar last week with a group of people. We came for the truffle pasta and the steak tartare mainly. The server refused to wrap up our extra steak tartare which I planned on taking home for my wife. Tonight my wife attempted to order the steak tartare for takeout. Gilt bar cancelled her order after it showed for 30 minutes that it is being made. I have never encountered an upscale restaurant refusing to deliver steak tartare or carpaccio!

Been here a couple times, tried different cocktails and food and have always been pleased. Service is great as well. It's a little spendy but well priced for the quality of food.  Get a reservation early.
The gnocchi, truffle pasta and side dishes were on point. The whiskey sours were very well done. Highly recommend coming here!

Visited Glit Bar yesterday for the first time, since it had so many great reviews I was looking forward to some delicious food but what happened next was an absolute nightmare! We started off with two cocktails a Gran Marnier mule and a Tequila old fashioned both drinks were off. The mule was super sour and the old fashioned tasted like cleaning products so I ended up sending them both back and ordered wine instead since you can't screw that up!  For appetizer we ordered their handmade truffle pasta which I have to ask who is the chef of the kitchen and how he would even allow for this dish to leave the kitchen is beyond me. I think that Olive Garden would have a better tasting pasta then what I was served! Look at the picture and tell me if this is your standard?
It was just ok.  Wasn't blown away by the food.  Should have gotten the cheeseburger because you know cant go wrong with that in this group. Prefer Bavette's nearby.
Amazing bacon homemade pastas and smoked salmon salad. Remarkable ambience Great for romantic dinner dates.
Love the atmosphere. Good food reasonable prices.
Great cocktails. The marrowbone was fantastic. Excellent service.
Food and drink were excellent. Our waitress was attentive. We were given a burger on the house which was suprising and delish.
Waited for almost an hour after being told it's a 15 minute wait. Finally left the place to find our dinner elsewhere.

Brief recap: 1. Thursday evening, packed at 5:30pm and stayed that way until after 8:30pm. 2. Careful when you enter revolving doors. Very dark and there may be patrons waiting to be seated you could stumble into. 3. Noise level, relatively loud, but you can have a conversation at a table. 4. Good wine, cocktails and beer selection. 5. Decent food menu. Can't go wrong with Au Cheval burger. Comes with delicious french fries. If on a date, you could split the burger and something else and likely be satisfied. 6. Dark lighting 7. Additional space in the basement (even darker, but still fun space). 8. Limited room at the actual bar. 9. Restrooms in the basement below bar. Photo booth on the way.
The Merlot for $20 was delicious. Vodka pasta, chicken and smashed potatoes were all spot on. Would definitely recommend this place to anyone coming to Chicago!
If we lived in the city. This would be in my ten ten places to visit. Love the inside decor.  And good food and drinks.

It's dark so good for trysts, hostage swaps and brooding in the corner whole writing dark poetry. Drinks are delicious, but pricey can get crowded. Personally I prefer sister Bavettes next door a little more but this is solid.
Food is delicious
Awesome food and drinks. Can be a little noisy on a busy day but still one of the best places for good steaks!
A very good spot to eat at. Bring a flashlight tho. Its a very dark dimly lit place, which makes seeing the menu hard. The food and drinks were good. Great selection of items.
A great place to take a date or to celebrate the occasion!

We enjoyed our dinner here. You need to plan ahead and make reservations at least a week in advance. Ask to have dessert in the library downstairs, there is a big difference in atmosphere between the restaurant and the library. You will enjoy the walk downstairs, through the narrow hall, and into the nondescript door. It felt like heading into a speakeasy. Super fun.
truffle is diiiiirty

Whoa!!! This place does not disappoint. We ordered a lot of food and everything was delicious. Standouts for me were the truffle pasta, smashed potatoes, steak tartare, green beans, and the chocolate pie (same as Bavette’s). Also they have a bottle of wine that’s $20 and it’s actually really good- and my friends and I are not usually in for cheap wine. Book your date, birthday, etc. at this restaurant now!
Great steak! Super sevice and atmosphere.
One of my favorite restaurants in Chicago. They make the best bone marrow in the world, bar none.
Service and door were both great. I loved the interior look of the place, the drinks and the slightly overpriced photobooth. I would definitely return to done here and take more pictures!
My husband and I came here for the first time this weekend and LOVED the experience. The pasta was delicious and the service was great!
The best mussels we have ever had! The atmosphere was romantic and moody. The drinks were great.  We will be going back only with a larger group ♡
Food is excellent and very nice ambiance
Nice, classy, date night spot.

Went to this place on a tuesday night at around 7 30 pm. It was jam packed. Got to sit down at around 8 30 pm. My wife and I ordered the vegetarian ( parmodoro and the vodka pasta). Both of them were delicious.i loved the vodka rigatoni better , the sauce they used was amazing. The portion size of the pasta were on thr smaller side . I also ordered moscow mule and it was a total RIPOFF. The mug was 70% filled with ice and hardly had alcohol. Tried the warm brownis for dessert and liked it. The service was not the best , could have been more responsive . Will surely come here again for their vegetarian pasta , hope they improve their service then.
The food was fantastic and service was impeccable.  The atmosphere was great as I loved the dark wood and low lights.  Can't wait to return next time we visit Chicago.

Love the atmosphere, but I wish there was more space between the tables. There's a coat check as well. Prices are high for the pasta--though handmade, I wish I got more for my money on all menu items. Great for a once and a while treat though.
Loved the food, I had the Truffle bucatini pasta and pretty much devoured everything in my plate. It was a bit dark and very loud for my taste otherwise I really liked the place

This has been one of my favorite restaurants for years. I came back for the first time in a while and couldn’t have been more disappointed. The cocktails and burrata were as delicious as ever. The fried chicken was a salty disgusting unappetizing mess and so was the bolognese.

It was my first night out in Chicago with my fiancé. We had the garlic focaccia to start. My fiancé got the ribeye and I had the fried chicken. The food was amazing. I had more than a few bites of my fiancés ribeye because it was amazing. We also got the chocolate cake on the house since we were celebrating our engagement. Our waiter was Wesley and he did an amazing job making it a memorable visit.
The food was fantastic and service was impeccable.  The atmosphere was great as I loved the dark wood and low lights.  Can't wait to return next time we visit Chicago.
I went there after 24 hours without sleeping (I’m come from paris) so my experience is a bit difficult.  but, the kindness and the hospitality of the team touched me a lot. I’ll be back, awake ; )
Great atmosphere, drinks and food!
Waitress was horrible

Love this place. The dim lighting of this place takes it to a different level. Make sure to notice the Edison bulbs. Make a reservation ahead of time and you should be good to go. Staff is super responsive and nice. And if you want, ask to go to The Library.
Very warm and personal atmosphere. We had the garlic bread and pasta - one of the most delicious truffle pastas I've ever had! We had a res and we were seated very quickly. Service was wonderful.

I’ve thrown a party here, it was great a few Years ago Not sure if it’s under new management, but nothing tastes the same. The cocktails, hell even the menu it was difficult to choose nothing made me want to try it. I came to this place a lot! Every time I came to town I’ve shared on social media, never again

Yes! This place is so good.  The short: expansive drink menu, reasonably priced delicious food, sultry ambiance and good service.  The long: Came here with a group of four friends and had a great experience from start to finish. We had a Friday 8pm reservation and were seated at a window seat immediately. Our waitress quickly came over with our drink menus which I always appreciate. I ordered the Spanish Old Fashioned which was really nice. It had a slight twist but was not too out of the ordinary.  For appetizers we ordered the garlic, salmon cesar salad and the beef tartar. The salmon salad was delicious and I loved how you could order half portions of all the salads. The garlic oil and bread was good however I wish there was a greater clove to oil ratio. I did not try the tartar but the table loved it.  For dinner we split the orecchiette and the truffle pasta. They were both super flavorful and the pasta was cooked perfectly al dente. I highly recommend both of these dishes. They are portioned very nice to split. We had also ordered the mashed potatoes but our waitress forget to bring them to the table which was fine with me since I was pleasantly full.  Overall, Gilt bar is a wonderful place to share a couple of dishes with good friends. I would definitely return here in the near future  P.S. if you're reading this review, Josh, you're a true toastmaster
Excellent place for some dinner a sweet treat for dessert. Recommended if your by that area.
Good times
Great spot.  Solid food
AWESOME bartenders and even better food. Downstairs is a hidden gem.

The food was delicious...kudos to the chef(s). Both my husband and I agree, would have gotten five stars but the service was a little off. Our server was not personable at all....didn’t bother to have an opening conversation when she introduced herself, which would have helped her to find out we were celebrating my birthday. Although my husband mentioned the special occasion to the hostess, it seems it wasn’t passed on either to make our dining experience special. Lastly, when my husband reserved he also noted on the reservation. So I found it odd that three other tables were brought out a special desert with sparkling candles....but not our table. 🤔
Very nice, up scale with good food and drinks!
Brilliant establishment, amazing service and a menu to satisfy anyone. The atmosphere is dark, elegant and hip

A variety of shared plates including mussels and bone marrow. This restaurant boasts an intimate atmosphere for diners with dim lighting and booths for small groups to sit in. We enjoyed a few different varieties of pasta; all were great!

I simply love this place. The theme of this bar is dark which is really lit. I have been visited this bar usually on weekends. The service was excellent. Food always superb. Highly recommend the fried chicken, and salmon.

It's kind of dark and loud. Food and drinks are excellent. The steak was even better when you dip it in the fried chicken gravy. The herb salt was meh. Yes we had both the fried chicken and steak at the same time.
My best friend daughter had her wedding there it was nice
Love the venue! Quality food & excellent cocktails.

I love everything about Gilt Bar, and it's my go-to place for any special event, whether it's a birthday or a date night out. When I say I love everything, I literally mean everything--the food and drinks, impeccable service and ambiance, and the fact that they have a speakeasy and photo booth downstairs.  There's something for everyone on the menu here. But, I've been here several times and I ALWAYS get the truffle pasta. The bucatini is perfectly al dente, and the truffle flavor is so strong. Other dishes I've really enjoyed are the pappardelle, gnocchi, the giant meatball, brussel sprouts, and any dessert that comes with ice cream. They have the smoothest ice cream ever. If you get the single scoop ice cream, it actually comes with two scoops! The drinks here are great as well. I tend to like sweeter drinks more and have gotten the Airmail a couple of times as well as the Bee's Knees and Lillet Rose. Their negronis are great too.  The people here are always so attentive and accommodating, and the decor is beautiful.  Tip--even if you don't have a reservation for the Library speakeasy below the restaurant, you can ask the hostess about doing dessert and drinks there. They are usually super accommodating about it, and will schedule it in for you after dinner.
The food is excellent. Service stellar. Recommended
We went here for our wedding anniversary. Everything we ordered was amazing. Atmosphere was great. We were very happy. Get a slice of pie for dessert. The crust was ridiculously good!
Closes a bit early on weeknights but great low-lit vibes and great drinks!

Wonderful dinner recommended to us by a native Chicagoan. Great ambiance, good cocktails, yummy food. We got the burrata and vodka pasta (got the pasta in a “half” portion - loved having that option). Pro tip: make sure you go to the bathroom, it’s an experience 😉
The food was fantastic and service was impeccable.  The atmosphere was great as I loved the dark wood and low lights.  Can't wait to return next time we visit Chicago.
Very intimate library seating. Service and food excellent
Great ambience and lovely hostesses. Would definitely visit again

Great service and wonderful food. The only issue I had was with the lights - it was extremely dark and very hard to see anything (I used effect to make all my pictures brighter). Also the way to the restrooms is a bit creepy.  But overall I had a good time.
Awesome places. The food and drinks are excellent.
Outstanding!
The food was okay but our cacio e Pepe tasted like the sauce was burned? It was odd and did not taste good. The staff is wonderful and helpful and the cocktails are great.
Low lighting with upbeat music made for an interesting combination.  Separate Vegan and Gluten free menus.  Moscow Mule was the best I have ever had.
Really great cocktails and speakeasy vibe.
No words to describe it . I just love the food , cocktail , service ill give them 10 stars instead.. great place for a date

Service staff were fantastic. Started out with bone marrow which was a first for me. It was ok. The red onion jam that came with it was the star. Our main courses were out of this world. I had the truffle pasta which was creamy, salty, and earthy from the tuffles. So good! My wife had the grilled chicken with lemon au jus. It was moist with a fantastic crust.
Very good atmosphere. Simple menu. Food was delicious. Service was good.
Great atmosphere and very stylish place. The bartenders really know what theyr'e doing.

very cool ambiance, was seated in the “library” downstairs and was very nice & quiet. loved how they actually make it look like a library, food was really good. only things that irked me was the lighting, it is so so dark you can barely see people around you and the menus especially. they could brighten it up just a bit.

Started with the beet salad, which was really good. And my wife was happy because it had feta and not goat cheese like most others.  One of the better steaks I've had in a while, great char and well seasoned.   Oddly enough the smashed potatoes were the star of the show.  There was a richness from the chicken au jus that put them over the top.  Burger was very good, wouldn't give it the edge over Au Cheval but not far behind.  Truffle pasta was a little disappointing, dare I say too much truffle.  Homemade noodles were great, just don't think they nailed the sauce.  Would definitely go back.
Amazing vodka pasta & skillet cookie dessert. The broccoli pesto pasta was a little too oily.
Great food, a little dark inside
The food is amazing!

1) The food was awesome. 2) Service was excellent. 3) This is what sets Gilt Bar aside from other restaurants:  My husband has advanced Parkinson’s. He needs a transport wheelchair for any distance, yet can still  walk some on his own. Narrow doorways cause him to have complete leg freezing. When we entered and left, he could not walk through the entrance and it was too narrow for the wheelchair. Amor (sp ?) gently helped him walk in with soft encouragement. When we left, he was extremely tired and Amor did an unbelievable job of helping me get him outside. When she gently held his hand to guide him out, I was so touched.
A favorite evening place of mine. The service was very friendly and attentive. The bill was reasonable I would say. I see why this place has a lot of good reviews.
Fantastic atmosphere, service, and food.
i had a cousin come into town and she asked me to go back here. the bill was reasonable i would say. food is similar to a place in san francisco i loved.
Really good flavor profiles (the salt not withstanding).  Best meatball I've had in awhile. Really all of the dishes contained too much salt for our tastes.

This is my new favorite hh spot. Yay!  I really like the vibe of the place.  The specialty drinks are all good and the prices are NOT outrageous.  Their use of gins, bourbons, and juices, etc. mmmm, so good.  AND their wine pours...ooh soo generous! Yes! Bartenders are super nice and patient.
Great food.
Amazing
Love going here for date nights out! Perfect atmosphere

Went on a coworkers recommendation, dimly lit and a little crowded, but that won’t get in between me and the best steak I’ve EVER had. Ribeye was PERFECTION. Bernaise allowed it to transcend. If crowds make you nervous, try to go early. Just make sure you go. It’s worth it.  Also, ask the bartenders if the drink menu feels like Greek to you, as it did to me. They aren’t snooty and deliver some magical concoctions.
Really love the vibe here. Their Sazerac is excellent, probably my favorite in the city.

I've been coming here for years and it's always been 5 stars until recently. The service has taken a nosedive. In addition to having no passion or information for the spirits, the last couple times I came here straight from work and was immediately sized up for not dressing like I live in the neighborhood. This resulted in my table being mostly ignored and drink menus being taken away abruptly. Well, message received and sorry for your loss. I would have gladly ordered several more rounds of drinks and sides, but can take a hint when my kind are not welcome.
Always a good time!
Absolutely the best cornbread, steak, and potatoes I've ever had.  Will definitely be back!

This is one of my favourite Chicago restaurant. I always order bone marrow and beef tartar- so good!!! Pasta is also very tasty. The only thing is it is always very dark (but beautiful) and maybe the music is too loud (the best if you don’t want to talk but enjoy food).

The food and atmosphere was incredible! I ordered the Burrata as an appetizer, 10/10. I really enjoyed my meal here, but the deserts were not great. The skillet cookie was so gooey it might as well have been raw. I also was disappointed with the service received. Everything took a long time to come. We order drinks and didn’t receive them until after the food was there. Our waitress seemed to be very busy and was not very attentive. I would go back, but I probably would return for a special occasion
Incredible service, absolutely delicious food, lovely cozy environment, I can’t wait to come back here! Perfect for romantic dinner or intimate night with friends.
(Translated by Google) Rico rich and well cared for  (Original) Rico rico y bien atendido
Great food, great service and great ambiance
One of the best spots in Chicago
The truffle pasta is to die for!!
We went here for our wedding anniversary. Everything we ordered was amazing. Atmosphere was great. We were very happy. Get a slice of pie for dessert. The crust was ridiculously good!

Absolutely one of my favorite stops in River North. The environment was classy, warm, and lively. We visited while on our honeymoon, and it was the perfect place to have a romantic, celebratory evening. I ordered the kale Caesar salad, rib eye steak, French fries, as well as a brandy Alexander; I relished all of it.  The prices align with the superb quality of the food. If you love delicious, savory plates and a magical atmosphere, The Gilt is the place for you.
A great date place and anniversary. Fabulous food and great drinks. Ambiance inviting and cozy.
Great food and fantastic atmosphere. Perfect place for a date night.
Best steak I have had in a long time.  Pork belly was also amazing
LOVED this experience! Great food and interesting drinks. Great service.

I don't know if I have enough words to tell everyone how amazing this place is! The food alone, I'd back for in a heart beat. It's the perfect atmosphere for a romantic date night, to a simple night out with the girls. The menu is limited, but you can tell they take pride in the food they make. It keeps things for being overwhelming. The drinks are fun and delicious! We tried the Paten En Croute, the tenderloin steak tartare, and the gnocchi al forno. All so incredible! The steak tartare was so delicious! If you are on the fence about giving it a try, do it for your taste buds! And always get a few of the appetizers, go big or go home they say! Oh, and don't skip dessert! I can't wait to go visit again!
Cozy and romantic ambiance. The giant meatball as a starter is a must! Delicious cocktails and the homemade pasta doesn't dissapoint. Also, fantastic service. We will be back!
Seriously, the best restaurant in the neighborhood. Everything on the menu is amazing and the cocktails are the best in town.
I have been to Gilt Bar a number of times, and the food is consistently excellent! The drinks are also fantastic, and the staff is pleasant and attentive.
Place has gone down the drain.  Over priced and it’s just not that good anymore.

Excellent drinks, excellent food, and some of the best chocolate pie I’ve ever had- and I don’t normally like chocolate pie. Been here several times and each one we’ve had a great experience...though the wait has been lengthy it’s always worth it to enjoy this wonderful atmosphere.

However the service is amazing, staff is nice and helpful.

One of the greatest places to check out in Chicago, great ambient, food is good, cocktails are good and service is fast. Expect a long wait time if you have a big party, I recommend checking it out on a weekday if you can, it tends to be dark inside but that’s all part of the experience.

My husband took me here for our anniversary in August because I love speakeasys and they have one in the basement. He made reservations for dinner before hand and told the host how excited he was to go to the speakeasy. We weren't told until we got there that the speakeasy was closed for the night for a private event. We were a little disapointed but still wanted to enjoy dinner. It is VERY dark inside which made reading the menus a little difficult but it was also romantic. The decor is very vintage and very cool. Our server was very nice. I got the pan roasted white fish and my husband got the pork belly. Our food was a little cold when it got to us and neither of us were really impressed. I have heard so many wonderful things about Gilt bar and I hope we came here to eat on an off day and we are planning to give dinner another try.  Unfortunately we did come back a few nights ago while we were in town. We had dinner reservations somewhere else but I was still hoping to check out the Library speakeasy so we stopped in for drinks. When we got there we were told that it was currently full but it shouldn't be too long before we could go in so we were seated on a couch with another couple to wait. We got a few drinks while we were waiting and wound up sitting there for almost 3 hours before we gave up and left.
Huge gnocchi fan and this place just nails it!!

I came here last night (Friday) for dinner and drinks with a friend. We had an 8:45 reservation. I got there at 8:40. Wasn't seated until 9:25. Had to keep reminding the host stand of my name and reservation each time I checked in to ask when we would be seated although we were literally standing in their faces the whole time. Once we were seated, the manager was nice enough to offer a complimentary appetizer. My friend chose the bone marrow, which I was not a fan of. We also tried the cornbread which was decent. My friend had the pork belly entree and enjoyed it but noted it was mostly fat. I had the salmon which was nicely seasoned but I was annoyed it was $25 for literally just the fillet (sides a la carte). Highlight of the experience were definitely the drinks and the downstairs library room. I had about four of the bee's knees which were delightful. I would come back but just for drinks.

Either way you'll look forward to going back again & again.

I highly recommend eating at Gilt Bar as soon as you can. I can not wait to go back myself.

However, people and the staff should know how she’s treating certain guest and to next time make sure everyone feels welcomed.

We were served small dishes of excellent food on stacks of decorative "library" books. Their steak is excellent, as are the donuts.  The velvet seating in semicircular booths made for a great environment. The room could comfortably handle 30 people.
Nice dark ambiance in here. Our food was delicious. They really know how to make a good cocktail.

My first trip to Chicago and I felt so incredibly lucky to visit Gilt Bar the last night before its upcoming renovations in January (over now)! This bar is everything you could imagine for an intimate and vintage venue for downtown Chicago.  As it was a Saturday night, it was very busy, but we were lucky enough to find two seats at the bar! They had really fun drinks and the bartender was very nice. As busy as they were, you could tell everyone was hustling and we never had to wait long for drinks or food. It is loud and fun, and every brief encounter with either a customer or server was great.  We didn't order too much, which we completely regret now! We shared the truffle pasta because of all the many yelp reviews before - and oh my goodness... My husband and I were so impressed with the rich and delicious flavors in this pasta dish! Usually, my husband will gulp down all of his food. He definitely took the time to enjoy every bite of this dish.  We enjoyed it so much we wanted to visit again (2 day trip); however learned that they were closing temporarily for renovations (they mentioned 2 wks). Yes, we were saddened by the news but also so grateful for running into this place and getting to experience it! We will be back!

Bartenders are pros and do justice to classics, Martinis, Manhattans, Cosmo, whatever. Food is always outstanding, although a la carte is not my favorite... It's not about cost, I'd just rather leave pairing of sides to the professionals. I wish they'd correct that. But the attraction is the ambiance... dark, hip, cool, and even a bit romantic making me regret traveling alone. So many great restaurants in Chicago but Gilt is always a must for me. Always leave wanting to tell someone about it, so... there you have it.

I adore Gilt Bar. I've been several times for a delightful meal and cocktails. If you like garlic (or are obsessed like me :-)), you MUST try the roasted garlic on toast. The bone marrow is also an excellent starter that I get on special …
The library downstairs has a great, low-lit, intimate vibe that's perfect for a date, get together, or for drinks before hitting the town.
Great atmosphere. Fair priced drinks. Great music. Fun photobooth downstairs!

Such a huge fan of Gilt Bar.  Of course they have amazing drinks but their food is even better.  The Steak Tartare is amazing and their Mussels could be some of the absolute best in the city.  You can't forget to try their Chicken entree but make sure to order a side of fries and brussel sprouts!  One of my go to places in Chicago, you can't go wrong with anything.  Plus the location, service, and incredibly reasonable price are all perfect.
